Function Reference/debug fopen « WordPress Codex
-----------

Open the file handle for debugging.

This function is used for XMLRPC feature, but it is general purpose
enough to be used in anywhere.

Usage
-----

` <?php debug_fopen( $filename, $mode ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$filename` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) File path to debug file.
    Default: *None*

 `$mode` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Same as fopen() mode parameter.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(bool)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   resource

Change Log
----------

Since: [0.71](/Version_0.71 "Version 0.71")

Source File
-----------

`debug_fopen()` is located in `wp-includes/functions.php`

